HEADWORD: Replica
<hw>Rep"li*ca</hw> <pr>(r?p"l?-k?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[It. See
<er>Reply</er>, <pos>v. & n.</pos>]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Fine Arts)</fld> <def>A copy of a work of art, as
of a picture or statue, made by the maker of the original.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Mus.)</fld> <def>Repetition.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Replicant</ent>⟦br⟧
